{"id":14881625,"mediaExerciseId":"8658a3ee-dd8a-48b7-abe5-3eb0cbfb612b","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"18","chapterTitle":"Short-Term Finance and Planning","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"18.5","sectionTitle":"Short-Term Borrowing","pageNumber":627,"solutions":[{"id":5990109,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This exercise requires us to identify the two basic forms of short-term financing and two types of secured loans. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/6f3f25ad8958056edf82c2b9f155d632/e4386b89f656dfe5a8c590e9d203b18d/lateximg_large.png","width":1013},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/6f3f25ad8958056edf82c2b9f155d632/e4386b89f656dfe5a8c590e9d203b18d/lateximg.png","width":506}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement 18.5a\n\nThe two basic forms of short-term financing are:\n\n1. Unsecured Loans\n2. Secured Loans","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"1. **Unsecured Loans** are short-term financing that do not require any collateral other than the debtor's creditworthiness. In addition, unsecured borrowers does not need to pledge specific assets to borrow. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/6f3f25ad8958056edf82c2b9f155d632/7bd88e83bdefb39d31573d37316bc85e/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/6f3f25ad8958056edf82c2b9f155d632/7bd88e83bdefb39d31573d37316bc85e/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"2. **Secured Loans** - are short-term financing that requires collateral or pledges specific assets. If some cases, if the borrower is unable to repay his loan, the lender may seize the collateral assets.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/6f3f25ad8958056edf82c2b9f155d632/45d54d72e687e64459a2ebfc3bb09141/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/6f3f25ad8958056edf82c2b9f155d632/45d54d72e687e64459a2ebfc3bb09141/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement 18.5b\n\nThe two types of secured short-term loans are:\n\n1. Accounts Receivable Financing \n2. Inventory Loans\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"1. **Accounts Receivable Financing** is a secured short-term loan that includes assigning receivables or factoring receivables. This loan enables a company to receive an early payment on unpaid invoices.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/6f3f25ad8958056edf82c2b9f155d632/04bb9c4c8d7693bbd0ef23b1d726c1b7/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/6f3f25ad8958056edf82c2b9f155d632/04bb9c4c8d7693bbd0ef23b1d726c1b7/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"2. **Inventory Loans** is a secured short-term loan that is acquired by a company to purchase goods or products. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/6f3f25ad8958056edf82c2b9f155d632/ecda27d648e02ba4404ba2a7695708cc/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/06/6f3f25ad8958056edf82c2b9f155d632/ecda27d648e02ba4404ba2a7695708cc/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"16ad17d6-1363-45aa-9be8-40628fc193f0","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":7}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881626,"exerciseName":"6","page":628,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"8d2addc2-a0c5-4afb-9db0-7ecde336bf23","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-18-exercises-6-8d2addc2-a0c5-4afb-9db0-7ecde336bf23"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881624,"exerciseName":"4","page":623,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"0f7146ab-7d99-421e-b92b-7df12d2b834c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-18-exercises-4-0f7146ab-7d99-421e-b92b-7df12d2b834c"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-18-exercises-5-8658a3ee-dd8a-48b7-abe5-3eb0cbfb612b"}